com.serena.dmclient.objects
Interface ReleaseTemplate

All Superinterfaces:
DimensionsObject
public interface ReleaseTemplate
extends DimensionsObject

Represents a Dimensions Release Template.

A release template is defined as a set of rules or criteria whose purpose is to limit the items to be selected for inclusion in a release. In PVCS Dimensions, releases are created subject to the rules specified in a Release Template. A rule is defined against a part structure and item type, and specifies the conditions the item must satisfy in order for it to be included in the release.

Note: Release templates are defined at a global (base database) level and are not associated with a specific product. A Dimensions product is only used to restrict the list the list of item types when defining a new template, or editing the details of an existing one.
